node.text:
#ad My easy, go-to Sunday morning breakfast (especially for when I need more energy for an active day):

Ingredients:
- 8‚Äù flour tortilla
- 2 eggs
- 1 cup spinach
- 1/4 cup black beans
- 1/4 California avocado @ca_avocados 
- 2 tbsp shredded Monterey Jack cheese
- Hot sauce
- Salsa (for dipping, if desired)

Instructions:
- Whisk 2 eggs, 1 tbsp water, and salt, pepper
- Add black beans to a nonstick skillet and season with cumin, oregano, and garlic powder. Cook black beans until warmed through (~3 min). Remove beans and place in bowl.
- Use same pan and cook spinach until wilted. Pour in eggs and scramble until cooked.
- Assemble the burrito: Top tortilla with scrambled eggs and spinach, black beans, avocado, cheese, and hot sauce.
- Fold the bottom flap of the burrito up and over the filling, tucking the sides and the filling as you roll the burrito.
- Place burrito back in a pan and cook each side until golden brown.

Notes
- You can opt for a lower carb tortilla if you need to limit carb and sodium
- Feel free to experiment and add in different veggies, such as bell peppers and onions

#breakfastburrito #avocado #CaliforniaAvocados #avoCAdos

node.text:
My cookbook, So Easy So Good, is officially a #2 NYT Bestseller üò≠‚ù§Ô∏è

Before my NYC event yesterday, I met with my team at a nearby restaurant. I thought we were all just hanging out and celebrating the launch of the book when @justcooknyc , my editor, informed me that he had just received the NYT Bestseller list hours before it was released to the public. I knew we were going to find out whether I had made the list that day, but I had no idea it would be in that moment, in that restaurant, around the very people who helped make that dream come true. 

I‚Äôm still shaking and tearing up writing this. It‚Äôs difficult to convey gratitude when something you never thought would happen‚Ä¶ actually happens. But this didn‚Äôt happen because of me ‚Äì it happened because of you.

To quote the first page of the book, ‚ÄúThis book is dedicated to my online community. Thank you for inspiring me and encouraging me every day. This book is as much yours as it is mine.‚Äù 

Thank you. I am forever grateful.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Kylie Sakaida on August 28, 2024.

node.text:
A sneak peek of my new cookbook: SO EASY SO GOOD (available for pre-order now)!! 

I turned 29 years old today and could not be more grateful to finally be able to talk publicly about a project I‚Äôve been working on since I was 26 but have dreamt about since I was 16. If you‚Äôre reading this, thank you for being here and making this possible.

I‚Äôm so proud of this project, and I can‚Äôt wait for you all to see it ü•π

Also, I want to give the biggest thank you to my team for helping me bring this dream to life @_simonelement @justcooknyc @brittanymaxwell.x @lme.in.nyc @lauren.deen @kteig @davidkoungphoto @carrieannpurcell @aliciabuszczak @danielaswamp

What I stock in my fridge for quick, balanced meals #FactorPartner

Some weeks I don‚Äôt have the energy to plan, shop, and cook balanced meals. That‚Äôs where a meal delivery service like @factormeals makes life so much easier!

‚úÖ Convenience: No grocery runs or late-night takeout. Meals are ready in minutes!‚Ä®‚úÖ Nutrition: Designed by dietitians and crafted by chefs, so I know I‚Äôm getting balanced protein, carbs, and veggies.‚Ä®‚úÖ Variety: I get to try dishes I wouldn‚Äôt usually cook at home. There are 100+ meals to choose from, but this week‚Äôs box included:
‚ÅÉ Roasted red pepper filet mignon with tortellini primavera and lemon garlic butter
‚ÅÉ Thai yellow curry chicken with ginger rice, broccoli, curried carrots, and chili lime peanuts
‚ÅÉ Blackened salmon with smoked gouda cauliflower ‚Äúgrits‚Äù and broccoli
‚ÅÉ African peanut curry with tofu, veggie rice, sweet potatoes, broccoli, and red peppers
‚ÅÉ Garlic herb chicken with vegetable risotto and roasted green beans
‚ÅÉ Braised pork and lentil medley with creamy jus, kale, and garlic broccoli

Having these stocked in my fridge makes healthy eating simple, realistic, and something I can stick to. Link for the offer is in my bio! Use code KYLIESAKAIDA for 50% off your order.

One per box with active subscription. Free meals applied as discount on first box. New or returning subscribers only. Varies by plan.

Lemon Balsamic Chicken, Sweet Corn & Avocado Salad, made with Fresh Express American Blend. #ad

Complicated salads can be time-consuming, but Fresh Express makes it so easy to throw together something fresh, flavorful, and actually satisfying!

This salad is a bright, bold summer bowl with lemon balsamic chicken, sweet corn, creamy avocado, tangy pickled onions, and salty cotija cheese, all served over a crisp bed of Fresh Express American Blend, which includes a mix of iceberg, romaine, carrots, red cabbage, and radishes. It‚Äôs one of my summer go-to‚Äôs and easier to make than you‚Äôd expect! 

Show me how you Express Yourself with @yourfreshexpresssalad! Find my full recipe at FreshExpress.com

 
#summerrecipes #salad #FreshExpress #ExpressYourself

node.text:
One of my favorite breakfasts featuring one of my favorite fruits: mangoes! @mangoboard #ad

Not only are they delicious and perfectly sweet, but they‚Äôre also have vitamin C and fiber, which can help keep you full and support digestion

Ingredients (serves 4):
‚ÅÉ 2 ripe mangoes, peeled and diced
‚ÅÉ 1 cup milk
‚ÅÉ ¬Ω cup plain Greek yogurt
‚ÅÉ 1/2 cup unsweetened coconut milk
‚ÅÉ 1.5 tbsp maple syrup or honey
‚ÅÉ 1 tsp vanilla extract
‚ÅÉ 1/2 cup chia seeds
‚ÅÉ 1/4 cup unsweetened shredded coconut (for garnish)
‚ÅÉ 1/4 cup chopped pistachios or almonds (optional, for crunch)

Instructions:
‚ÅÉ In a blender, combine mango, milk, greek yogurt, coconut milk, maple syrup, and vanilla extract for the base.
‚ÅÉ Pour the mango mixture into a bowl or jar and stir in chia seeds until well combined. Let sit for 5 minutes, then stir again to prevent clumping.
‚ÅÉ Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours (or overnight) until thickened.
‚ÅÉ When ready to serve, transfer chia pudding mixture into jars and top with more diced mango, shredded coconut, and nuts.

#MangoJoyRide #MangoMadeEasy #MangoMagic

Another higher fiber, higher protein rice I love to make! 

Just to clarify, you can totally use bone broth, chicken broth, and any other seasonings! But I prefer no seasonings since I personally use white rice as a blank canvas for a lot of my Asian meals :) 

This recipe is pretty simple and straightforward, but you can find the full written recipe on my free website (link in bio or comment ‚ÄúRECIPE‚Äù and I‚Äôll DM it to you)

#fiber #EasyRecipe
